# Observed OTUs - Histogram: Distribution of total number of bacterial species within the Asthma-BLT population
## Density is different with count: relative frequency = count/total sample size = density * width of each bar (here is 2). e.g if density = 0.05, meaning relative frequency = 0.05*2=0.1, meaning 10% of sample siz

OTUs_overall_histogram <- ggplot(df_shape_histogram, aes(x=Genera))+ 
  geom_histogram(aes(y=..density..), binwidth = 1, alpha = 1, color="black", fill="#8491B4B2")+ # Can change "density" to "count" so you are able to see the frequency
  geom_density(alpha=0.3, fill="#8491B4B2")+
  geom_vline(aes(xintercept=median(Genera)), color="black", linetype="dashed", size=0.5)+
  scale_y_continuous(expand = expansion(mult = c(0, .1)))+
  labs(title="",x="No. of genera", y = "Density")+
  theme_bw() +
  theme(axis.text.x=element_text(colour="black", face="plain", size=10), 
        axis.text.y=element_text(colour="black", face="plain", size=10),
        axis.title.x=element_text(margin = margin(t = 10)),
        axis.title.y=element_text(margin = margin(r = 10)),
        axis.title = element_text(face="plain", size = 10),
        plot.title = element_text(size = 10, hjust = 0.5, face="plain"),
        panel.border = element_rect(color = "black",
                                    fill = NA,
                                    size = 1),
        panel.grid = element_blank(),
        legend.background = element_rect(color="transparent"),
        aspect.ratio = 1,
        plot.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent", colour = "transparent"))+
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(20,70), breaks = seq(20,70,10))

Shape for core taxa

Male

# Male group
df_all_Male <- df_all %>% 
  filter(Sex =="Male")

# WT group
df_WT <- df_all_Male %>% 
  filter (Genotype == "WT") 
## Taxa of which presence is more than 90%
df_presence_WT<- df_WT %>% 
  gather(Taxa, Abundance, -c(1:17)) %>% # transform to long table
  select(2,3,5,6,7,8,9,18,19) %>% 
  filter(Abundance != 0) %>% # save the taxa of which abundance is not equal to 0
  group_by(Taxa) %>% 
  summarise(n=n_distinct(SequenceID)) %>% #get number of samples that have non-zero abundance bacteria as grouped by bacteria# 
  mutate(n.sample=nrow(df_WT)) %>% 
  mutate(p=n/n.sample)

df_presence_core_WT<- df_presence_WT%>% 
  filter(p>=0.95)

## Taxa of which abundance is more than 0.01%
df_abundance_WT <- df_WT %>%
  gather(Taxa, Abundance, -c(1:17)) %>% # transform to long table
  select(2,3,5,6,7,8,9,18,19) %>%
  group_by(Taxa) %>% 
  summarise(mean_abundance=mean(Abundance,na.rm=T),
            median_abundance = median(Abundance,na.rm=T))

df_abundance_core_WT <- df_abundance_WT %>%
  filter(mean_abundance>0.0001) 

# KO group
df_KO <- df_all_Male %>% 
  filter (Genotype == "KO") 
## Taxa of which presence is more than 90%
df_presence_KO<- df_KO %>% 
  gather(Taxa, Abundance, -c(1:17)) %>% # transform to long table
  select(2,3,5,6,7,8,9,18,19) %>% 
  filter(Abundance != 0) %>% # save the taxa of which abundance is not equal to 0
  group_by(Taxa) %>% 
  summarise(n=n_distinct(SequenceID)) %>% #get number of samples that have non-zero abundance bacteria as grouped by bacteria# 
  mutate(n.sample=nrow(df_KO)) %>% 
  mutate(p=n/n.sample)

df_presence_core_KO<- df_presence_KO%>% 
  filter(p>=0.95)

## Taxa of which abundance is more than 0.01%
df_abundance_KO <- df_KO %>%
  gather(Taxa, Abundance, -c(1:17)) %>% # transform to long table
  select(2,3,5,6,7,8,9,18,19) %>%
  group_by(Taxa) %>% 
  summarise(mean_abundance=mean(Abundance,na.rm=T),
            median_abundance = median(Abundance,na.rm=T))

df_abundance_core_KO <- df_abundance_KO %>%
  filter(mean_abundance>0.0001) 

# Join the tables
df_all_WT <- left_join(df_presence_WT, df_abundance_WT, by="Taxa")
df_all_KO <- left_join(df_presence_KO, df_abundance_KO, by="Taxa")

df_for_core_WT <- inner_join(df_presence_core_WT, df_abundance_core_WT, by="Taxa")
df_for_core_KO <- inner_join(df_presence_core_KO, df_abundance_core_KO, by="Taxa")


# WT group
df_for_core_WT_100 <- df_for_core_WT %>% 
  mutate(Prevalence = p*100) %>% 
  mutate(Abundance = mean_abundance*100)

# KO group
df_for_core_KO_100 <- df_for_core_KO %>% 
  mutate(Prevalence = p*100) %>% 
  mutate(Abundance = mean_abundance*100)

# Save table
write_xlsx(df_all_WT, "df_all_WT_Male.xlsx")
write_xlsx(df_all_KO, "df_all_KO_Male.xlsx")
write_xlsx(df_for_core_WT, "df_for_core_WT_Male.xlsx")
write_xlsx(df_for_core_KO, "df_for_core_KO_Male.xlsx")


# Plot
genotypes_venn <- list(df_for_core_WT$Taxa,df_for_core_KO$Taxa)
names(genotypes_venn) <- c("WT Male", "KO Male")
ggvenn(genotypes_venn,
       fill_color = c("#3C5488B2","#7E6148B2"),
       fill_alpha = 0.7,
       stroke_size = 0.5, set_name_size = 6, digits=0,
       text_size = 5.5, text_color = "white")
